17/12/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The main contenders in the 2 January presidential election started their election campaigns Thursday (16 December). 
Incumbent President Stipe Mesic kicked off his bid with a rally in the small southern town of Vrgorac. 
His chief rival, Deputy Prime Minister Jadranka Kosor of the ruling HDZ party, started her campaign in Lipik, near her hometown of Pakrac. 
The latest polls indicate Mesic has about 45 per cent of public support, compared to 11 per cent for Kosor. 
(Vjesnik, Vecernji list - 17/12/04; HINA, HRT - 16/12/04)
